page.title: 08 DYSCARR WOOD LANGOLD
page.content: {Dyscarr wood}is a nature reserve.It is in{Langold}and mostly in{ {Nottinghamshire.}There is a path running through the wood and it is the border of{Nottinghamshire}and { {South Yorkshire.}There are a lot of flowers and different types of trees.The wood in June is full of cow parsley and wild garlic which smell like manure.Most of the trees are sycamores.We saw{robins, wrens {blackbirds.}We saw alot of butterflies:_{Cabbage {Whites,Peacocks. }There were tweets,whistles and chirps all around. The wood is owned by the Nottinghamshire Conservation Trust and they look after it as well.There were some workmen burning old wood.
